This recipe was so easy to make and the presentation quality was incredibly beautiful! Perfect for summer desserts; cool and refreshing for outdoor parties. I used peaches, blackberries, raspberries, strawberries, and kiwis.

Rating: 4
This recipe is so easy! The lemon cream cheese filling is so refreshing and light, and the presentation is just stunning. If you don't like the fruit suggested in the recipe, substitute with any fruit you enjoy, and it will still come out just perfect. The tart looks like a $35 tart that you might buy at Dean & Deluca, but it cost only a few dollars to make. Perfect for a special occassion. Perfect for fruit lovers! The glaze is just lovely, too. I made this four times already, and will be writing it into my permanent collection for future "last minute" pot lucks!

