Rating: 4
This is an excellent tart recipe--perhaps my favorite! I've made it about four times in the past few months, always to rave reviews. Plus, its absolutely beautiful. It looks like it took a ton of work, but is truly quick and easy to prepare. I also used strawberries rather than pineapple (I think it looks nicer with the contrast of green from the kiwi and orange from the mango). I used more than the 2 tablespoons of the apricot preserves because I like the glossy look. Again, an excellent, easy recipe!

Rating: 3
This is a great tart. I made it with 1 mango, 2 kiwis, and strawberries (I am afraid the strawberries took away the "tropical aspect" of the recipe). I used 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract instead of the vanilla extract alone. Since I do not really like store bought pie crust, I used the recipe for "Flaky Pie Crust" from this site. I'll certainly make this recipe again.

